
========================================================================
  g-SCALING — watch the entity get smarter as the substrate scales (toy, laptop)
========================================================================

  A. DIMENSION REACH — fixed features vs a LEARNED representation (cost-to-know, held-out):

      d |   fixed features |      learned rep
     ------------------------------------------
      1 |              300 |              300
      2 |              800 |              300
      3 |       WALL (inf) |              300
      4 |       WALL (inf) |              300
      5 |       WALL (inf) |              300

     -> fixed features wall at d=3; learned representation reaches further (wall d=>5).
        Same problem, newly solvable: the entity climbed by improving its REPRESENTATION.

  B. LANGUAGE REACH — does grounded communication hold as the vocabulary grows?

      vocab K |  samples-to-1st-comm |  zero-shot composition
     --------------------------------------------------------
            4 |                    6 |                 100%
            8 |                   39 |                  93%
           16 |                   89 |                  92%

     -> communication + zero-shot composition hold as the world grows (the channel scales).

========================================================================
  the lever is a better REPRESENTATION, not more parameters — that is the bet.
========================================================================
